<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56b49501-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s1948"><num value="1948">§ 1948.</num><heading> Marine safety curriculum</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Commandant shall ensure that professional courses of study in marine safety are provided at the Coast Guard Academy, and during other officer accession programs, to give Coast Guard cadets and other officer candidates a background and understanding of the marine safety program. These courses may include such topics as program history, vessel design and construction, vessel inspection, casualty investigation, and administrative law and regulations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56b49502-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tV/s525/a">Pub. L. 111–281, title V, § 525(a)</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2959">124 Stat. 2959</ref>, § 200; renumbered § 199 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/111/330/s1/7/A">Pub. L. 111–330, § 1(7)(A)</ref>, <date date="2010-12-22">Dec. 22, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3569">124 Stat. 3569</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/115/232/dC/tXXXV/s3531/c/11">Pub. L. 115–232, div. C, title XXXV, § 3531(c)(11)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/2320">132 Stat. 2320</ref>; renumbered § 1948, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s110/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 110(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4212">132 Stat. 4212</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
